 of the National Socialist past. Their works invoke, however, new questions: What happens when we cross the line between narration and documentation, and between memory and a musical piece? How does identification and fascination affect our reading of the text? What kind of ethical issues do these testimonies raise? As this volume shows, reading these musical biographies is both troubling and compelling since they 'fail' to come to terms with the past. In playing the haunting music that does not let us put the matter to rest, they call into question not only the exclusion of personal stories by official narratives, but also challenge writers' and readers' most intimate perspectives on an unmasterable past.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 16. Mai 2019) 0aGerman fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aMemory in literature. 0aMusic and literaturezAustriaxHistoryy20th century. 0aMusic and literaturezGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 4aErzählwissenschaft. 4aGerman culture. 4aHolocaust. 4aKultur / Deutschland. 4aMusical Poetics. 4aMusikalische Poetik. 4anarrative. 70(DE-601)1047563810(DE-588)4115345-5aNationalsozialismusgMotiv2gnd 70(DE-601)1052270130(DE-588)4193441-6aErinnerunggMotiv2gnd 70(DE-601)10582058X0(DE-588)4114652-9aMusikgMotiv2gnd 70(DE-601)1058304370(DE-588)4113292-0aDeutsch2gnd 70(DE-601)1062450150(DE-588)4035964-5aLiteratur2gnd 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2016z9783110485264oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831104604690 cprintz978311045795740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110460933423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110460933.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL 